            {
               "text": "### Mesoamerica: The Beginning\n\nMaps like those presented in the section *Continent: Africa* reflect historical divisions that have shaped the borders we recognize today. However, not all maps created by humans are intended to define borders. An example is the map in this section, which highlights a region known as Mesoamerica. This concept was not created by the Indigenous peoples of the region but was defined centuries later by anthropologist Paul Kirchhoff. He used this term to group cultures that shared common characteristics within a specific geographical area",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "2d720f02-051c-4469-b425-7d020f2c2f9b",
